Configuration is expected to be mounted /etc/trino as per https://github.com/trinodb/trino/blob/master/core/docker/README.md
Make sure all the config files are present in the right directory : https://trino.io/docs/current/security/password-file.html#password-authenticator-configuration

#Run trino
docker run -p 8080:8080 -e AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=minioadmin -e AWS_SECRET_KEY=minioadmin --network host --volume $PWD/trino/core/docker/default/etc:/etc/trino --name trino trinodb/trino

anisha@Anishas-MacBook-Pro Desktop % docker exec -it trino trino --user test
trino> select current_user;
 _col0
-------
 test
(1 row)


anisha@Anishas-MacBook-Pro Desktop % docker exec -it trino trino --user=test --password
Password:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Authentication using username/password requires HTTPS to be enabled
	at com.google.common.base.Preconditions.checkArgument(Preconditions.java:143)
	at io.trino.cli.QueryRunner.setupBasicAuth(QueryRunner.java:176)



References :
1/https://trino.io/docs/current/develop/system-access-control.html
2/Setup using : https://trino.io/docs/current/security/password-file.html#password-authenticator-configuration